-- England Beats Australia in One-Day Cricket Match, Takes 2-0 Lead in Series
-- Peter-Joseph Hegarty
-- 2010-06-24T21:04:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-24/england-beats-australia-in-one-day-cricket-match-takes-2-0-lead-in-series.html

          
          
             England beat Australia by four
wickets at Cardiff, Wales, today to take a 2-0 lead in the one-
day cricket series.  
 Australia totaled 239-7 in its 50 overs, including 86 not
out from Cameron White and 57 from Shane Watson. Stuart Broad
took 4-44.  
 England made 243-6 in 45.2 overs, Eoin Morgan getting 52,
captain Andrew Strauss 51 and Paul Collingwood 48. England also
won the first match by four wickets.  
 The third in a five-game series is in Manchester on June
27.  
          
          


  


        